@NODE "intro" "LimpidClock Guide"
@TOC "main"

@{B}Introduction@{UB}
@{B}============@{UB}

LimpidClock is a transparent clock and calendar. It shows the current time,
an analog clock and a calendar of the current month with today highlighted.

Needs Workbench 3.0+. On any WB below 3.5 it needs ClassAct, too.



@{B}Contact@{UB}
@{B}=======@{UB}

Please send suggestions and bug reports to @{B}thomas-rapp@web.de@{UB}

@ENDNODE
@NODE "install" "LimpidClock Guide"
@TOC "main"

@{B}Installation@{UB}
@{B}============@{UB}

There is an installer script for automatic installation.

To manually install it, 

 - drag the program icon to your WBStartup drawer.
 - copy the language catalog to locale:catalogs.


@ENDNODE
@NODE "menu" "LimpidClock Guide"
@TOC "main"


@{B}Menu Items@{UB}
@{B}==========@{UB}

@{B}Save settings@{UB}         Save the current window position and layout to the
                      program's icon.

@{B}Reset to last saved@{UB}   Reset all settings to the state when they were last
                      saved.

@{B}Reset to defaults@{UB}     Reset all settings to factory defaults

--------------------

@{B}Edit reminders@{UB}        Add or remove reminders

--------------------

@{B}Fixed position@{UB}        Don't allow to move the window.

@{B}No automatic refresh@{UB}  Disable automatic window refresh. Might be faster.

--------------------

@{B}Analog clock@{UB}          Enable the analog clock.

@{B}Digital clock@{UB}         Enable the digital clock.

@{B}Calendar@{UB}              Enable calendar

@{B}No shadow@{UB}             Disable drop shadow

@{B}No seconds@{UB}            Don't show seconds in digital and analog clock

@{B}Clock with AM/PM@{UB}      Select AM/PM format (as opposed to 24 hour format)

@{B}Show year@{UB}             Show the year number behind the month name

@{B}Show week numbers@{UB}     Show numbers of the weeks in the left of the calendar rows

--------------------

@{B}Select font@{UB}           Select font for calendar and digital clock

@{B}Adjust colors@{UB}         Change display colors

@{B}Appearance of analog clock@{UB}
                      Change many parameters of the analog clock.

@{B}Number of dots@{UB}        Choose how many dots are drawn around the analog clock.

@{B}Start week with@{UB}       Choose which weekday is the first in a week

@{B}Select sound@{UB}          Select sound files to be played every second resp.
                      every full hour. Leave the file name field empty to
                      play no sound.

@{B}Mute@{UB}                  Temporarily mute the sound.

@{B}Ring the hour bell accroding to the current time@{UB}
                      With this option disabled, the hour sound is played once
                      every hour. If the option is enabled, the hour sound is
                      played once at 1:00, twice at 2.00, three times at 3:00
                      and so on.

--------------------

@{B}Set task priority@{UB}     Change the priority of LimpidClock's task.

--------------------

@{B}About@{UB}                 Display information about LimpidClock

--------------------

@{B}Iconify@{UB}               Close clock window

@{B}Jump to pub screen@{UB}    Let the user choose a screen LimpidClock should run on

--------------------

@{B}Close@{UB}                 Quit the program

@ENDNODE
@NODE "config" "LimpidClock Guide"
@TOC "main"

@{B}Tooltypes@{UB}
@{B}=========@{UB}

@{B}TOOLPRI=@{UB}n                Set task priority for LimpidClock. Default is -20.

@{B}LEFT=@{UB}x                   x-position of the clock window (default = center of the screen)

@{B}TOP=@{UB}y                    y-position of the clock window (default = below the title bar)

@{B}DELAY=@{UB}n                  delay in ticks (1/50th second) before the window opens.
                         Adjust this so that the backdrop picture is ready before
                         the clock is drawn.

@{B}NOCLOCK@{UB}                  Don't show clock, only calendar.

@{B}NOCALENDAR@{UB}               Don't show calendar, only clock.

@{B}CLOCK=@{UB}n                  Choose clock layout:
                         1 = digital clock
                         2 = analog clock
                         4 = calendar
                         Add numbers to choose combinations. Default is 7 (show all).

@{B}AM_PM@{UB}                    Show clock in a.m./p.m. format (default is 24 hour format).

@{B}YEAR@{UB}                     Show year number behind month name

@{B}WEEKNUMBERS@{UB}              Show number of the week in the left of the calendar rows

@{B}STARTDAY=@{UB}n               Choose weekday the week starts with. 0 = Sunday, 1 = Monday etc. 
                         Default is 1 (Monday).

@{B}NOSHADOW@{UB}                 Don't draw drop shadow

@{B}NOSECONDS@{UB}                Don't show seconds in clocks

@{B}CLOCKSIZE=@{UB}n              Set size of analog clock. 0 means relative to font size (default).

@{B}NDOTS=@{UB}n                  Set number of dots around analog clock. Default is 60.

@{B}FIXEDPOSITION@{UB}            Don't allow to move the LimpidClock window.

@{B}SMARTREFRESH@{UB}             Disable automatic window refresh (might be faster)

@{B}PUBSCREEN=@{UB}name           Set the name of the public screen LimpidClock should
                         be opened on.

@{B}CLOCKFONT=@{UB}name/size      Choose font for digital clock seperately.

@{B}CALENDARFONT=@{UB}name/size   Choose font for calendar seperately.

@{B}SHADOWCOLOR=@{UB}rrggbb       set color for drop shadow

@{B}DIGICLOCKCOLOR=@{UB}Brrggbb   set color for digital clock

@{B}CLOCKDOTSCOLOR=@{UB}rrggbb    set color for dots around the analog clock

@{B}HOURPTRCOLOR=@{UB}rrggbb      set color for hour pointer in analog clock

@{B}MINPTRCOLOR=@{UB}rrggbb       set color for minutes pointer

@{B}SECPTRCOLOR=@{UB}rrggbb       set color for seconds pointer

@{B}MONTHCOLOR=@{UB}Brrggbb       set color for month name

@{B}WEEKDAYSCOLOR=@{UB}Brrggbb    set color for calendar headline

@{B}DAYSCOLOR=@{UB}Brrggbb        set color for days in calendar

@{B}TODAYCOLOR=@{UB}Brrggbb       set color for the highlighted day in the calendar

@{B}WEEKNOCOLOR=@{UB}Brrggbb      set color for the week numbers

color format: Brrggbb    B  : B = bold face, 0 or missing = normal
                         rr : hexadecimal red   (00 - ff)
                         gg : hexadecimal green (00 - ff)
                         bb : hexadecimal blue  (00 - ff)

@{B}SECSOUND=@{UB}filename        Choose sound to play every second.

@{B}HOURSOUND=@{UB}filename       Choose sound to play every full hour.

@{B}HOURCOUNT@{UB}                Ring the hour bell according to the current time
                         (otherwise it rings only once).

@{B}HOURPTRLENGTH=@{UB}n          Length of the hour pointer
@{B}HOURPTRWIDTH=@{UB}n           Width of the hour pointer
@{B}HOURPTRTAIL=@{UB}n            Length of the tail of the hour pointer

@{B}MINPTRLENGTH=@{UB}n           Length, width and tail of the minutes pointer
@{B}MINPTRWIDTH=@{UB}n
@{B}MINPTRTAIL=@{UB}n

@{B}SECPTRLENGTH=@{UB}n           Length, width and tail of the minutes pointer
@{B}SECPTRWIDTH=@{UB}n
@{B}SECPTRTAIL=@{UB}n             All lengths are in percent of the clock radius.

@{B}DOTS15SIZE=@{UB}n             Extension of the dots which mark full 15 minutes (3, 6 ,9 and 12)
@{B}DOTS5SIZE=@{UB}n              Extension of the dots which mark full 5 minutes
@{B}DOTS1SIZE=@{UB}n              Extension of the dots which mark all the other minutes in between

@{B}REMINDERFILE=@{UB}filename    File where reminders are stored. Default is S:LimpidClock.reminders

@{B}ALPHA=@{UB}n                  Transparency value for reminders in calendar. Default is 100.
                         Does only work on truecolor screen modes.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "reminders" "LimpidClock Guide"
@TOC "main"

@{B}Reminders@{UB}
@{B}=========@{UB}


Reminders work much like an alarm clock but with more options.

You can choose whether or not

- an alarm is sounded
- a message window appears

whenever the date and time of the reminder is reached or

- if the day of the reminder is highlighted in the calendar.

You can individually choose which part of date and time is compared to the
current time. So all possible types of reminders are possible, from a
simple alarm clock over highlighting of holidays to special sounds on
special days (e.g. friday the 13th or halloween).

To create a new reminder, just click on the repective day on the calendar.

A file with example reminders comes with the archive. Just copy
LimpidClock.reminders to the S directory on your boot drive and restart
LimpidClock to try it out.


@ENDNODE
@NODE "locale" "LimpidClock Guide"
@TOC "main"

@{B}Languages@{UB}
@{B}=========@{UB}

Unlike the first versions it uses its own locale catalog now. A German
catalog is included as well as the .cd and .ct files to create other
languages. Copy the catalog files to locale:catalogs or keep them in the
same directory as LimpidClock. Remember that with AmigaOS 4.0 the language
names are in english now. So for example you have to copy the german
catalog to locale:catalogs/german instead of locale:catalogs/deutsch.

Czech catalog by Miroslava Langrova.
Italian catalog by Samir Hawamdeh.
Polish catalogs by vOYtEC.
Russian catalog by Michael Malyshev.
Slovak catalog by Jan Zahurancik.
Spanish catalog by Javier de las Rivas.
Swedish catalog by Harry Samwel.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "tips" "LimpidClock Guide"
@TOC "main"

@{B}Usage notes@{UB}
@{B}===========@{UB}

- Doubleclick into the clock window to refresh the backdrop (in case it is
  garbled).

- Move it with the mouse to the position you like (if "Fixed position" is
  not checked)

- Run the program again to close it, or use the menu.

@ENDNODE
@NODE "history" "LimpidClock Guide"
@TOC "main"

@{B}History@{UB}
@{B}=======@{UB}

1.10:

- fixed transparency on CyberGFX
- added support for TTEngine
- option to change the number of dots around analog clock
- option to start week with sunday
- added sound options for seconds and hours


1.11:

- fixed crash when saving config
- fixed window size when removing digital clock
- fixed "no shadow" option
- fixed window size and clock position for big analog clock
- fixed "reset to defaults" - didn't do anything but flash the window
- fixed "reset to last saved" - didn't reset all options
- fixed error requester when ttengine.library is not available
- changed timer to be more accurate
- added option to hide seconds
- increased stack size in 68k icons


1.12:

- removed window activation on startup
- finally found a way to add automatic window refresh
- added option to show week numbers
- fixed clock being hidden behind WB window after reset WB


1.13:

- added option to disable automatic window refresh
- improved refresh speed
- added iconify option
- added options to change analog clock appearance
- fixed bug in changed prefs handling (Workbench screen could not be closed)
- added font requester for ttengine version if default fonts fail to open
- fixed bug when headline is smaller than numbers


1.14:

- added italian language to installer script
- bug fixed: calendar disappeared if LimpidClock was started at hh:mm:00


1.15:

- bug fixed: the main window always opened on the Workbench screen, although
  the background was taken from the specified public screen
- new option: play hour sound according to the current time
- new option: jump to public screen
- installer can automatically (re-)start LimpidClock after installation


1.16:

- bug fixed: didn't quit on Ctrl-C when iconified
- bug fixed: sounds were not freed
- gfx output is clipped to the window
- clock no longer freezes if time is changed backwards
- bug fixed: LimpidClock no longer becomes the active window on prefs changes
- added reminders
- bug fixed: week number was wrong when the first week belongs to the year before
- bug fixed: newicon image was not stored correctly
- added check for sufficient stack
- installer uses environment variable if current language is not recognised
- user can choose preferred installer language if the current language is not built in


@ENDNODE
